The South African Police Service has confirmed that Amy-Lee de Jager, who was reportedly kidnapped at her school on Monday morning, has been found. The six-year-old was reported kidnapped after four men allegedly snatched her from her mother at the Kollege Park Primary School in Vanderbijlpark. “Amy was found this morning and she is undergoing a medical examination at a local hospital,” said police spokesperson Vishnu Naidoo in a statement. He said an investigation into her disappearance and sudden reappearance is still ongoing. “It is our appeal that this investigation be allowed to take its course,” he said. – SAnews.gov.za 